# node_modules appears in the file tree when NO .gitignore suppresses it.
# SEV-3: file TREE shows node_modules; file PICKER hardcodes node_modules
# exclusion (app/picker.rs:98). Inconsistency between the two surfaces.
#
# Without .gitignore, the `ignore` crate has no built-in rule for node_modules,
# so it flows through to the tree.  TypeScript devs running `npm install` on a
# project that hasn't committed .gitignore will see node_modules flood the rail.
#
# Note: files must exist before the tree first builds, OR tree.refresh must be
# called.  The test uses shell to seed then tree.refresh to rescan.

shell mkdir -p node_modules/some-dep
shell echo '{}' > node_modules/some-dep/index.js
shell echo '{"name":"test","version":"1.0.0"}' > package.json
shell mkdir -p src
shell echo 'console.log("hi")' > src/index.ts

# No .gitignore present — trigger a rescan so the tree picks up the files.
command tree.refresh
wait 100

# After rescan, node_modules should appear in the tree rail.
expect screen contains "node_modules"
expect screen contains "src"
